SYMPTOM_TEXT: Died; Increased respirations (22 and labored at times); Pulse 105; 94% O2 on RA; Labored breathing at times; leukocytosis; elevated BUN; left lower lung congestion; elevated creatinine; Temperature of 102.0F; Redness on face; A spontaneous report was received from a nurse concerning a 92-year-old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced redness on face, increased respirations, labored breathing at times, temperature of 102F, pulse of 105, 94 percent O2, leukocytosis, elevated BUN, left lower lung congestion, elevated creatinine, and death.   The patient's medical history, as provided by the reporter, included dementia and reduced mobility.  No relevant concomitant medications were reported.   On 29 Dec 2020, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 30 Dec 2020, the patient began to experience redness on her face, increased respirations (reported as 22 and labored at times), pulse of 105, and 94 percent oxygen saturation on room air. The patient had a fever of 102 degrees Fahrenheit. Laboratory tests revealed a negative influenza swab, elevated white blood cell count of 14.1, elevated BUN at 113, and creatinine 2.7. Chest x-ray showed mild, left lower lung infiltrate.   On 31 Dec 2020, the patient went under hospice care per her family request..    Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not applicable.  The patient died on 01 Jan 2021, the cause of death was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 92-year-old, female subject with medical history of dementia and reduced mobility, who experienced the serious unexpected events of death, respiratory rate increased, heart rate increased, oxygen saturation decreased, elevated BUN, elevated creatinine, left lung congestion and dyspnoea and the non-serious events of erythema and pyrexia. The events of respiratory rate increased, heart rate increased, oxygen saturation decreased, dyspnoea, erythema and pyrexia occurred 2 days after the first dose of the study medication administration, and the event of death occurred 4 days after the first dose of the study medication administration. Very limited information regarding the events is available at this time and no definite diagnosis or autopsy report have been provided.  Additional information has been requested.; Reported Cause(s) of Death: Died

SYMPTOM_TEXT: An expired dose of Pediarix was given to six month old patient by a medical assistant working at our clinic who does not usually work at our facility, the medical assistant who gave the expired vaccine usually works at our sister office. The expired Pediarix had been left next to the unexpired vaccines by mistake and not isolated and marked like it should have been. The MA who gave the expired vaccine did not check the expiration date closely enough before giving the vaccine. I do the VFC reconciliations for our clinic, so I discovered this error while completing my January 2021 reconciliation. The patient who received the expired vaccine may need to repeat the vaccine if the patient is not immune. I will do a better job at identifying and isolating expired vaccines. The medical staff has been notified that they need to remember to check expiration dates on vaccines three times before administration, once when the vaccine is pulled from the fridge, second check while preparing the vaccine, and third check right before administration.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: At 0908, RRT was called at the post-vaccination monitoring area for an 89 y/o male that was experiencing dizziness after administration of the Pfizer vaccine at 0900. Client?s car was off, 4 RRT nurses responded to the scene with the E-kit, stethoscope, and pulse oximeter. Head-to-toe assessment done, all WNL. Reports a Sulfa allergy and denies taking any medications today. Initial vitals ? HR: 79, RR: 18, BP: 137/70, denies pain. Client reports that he fell once last week and once this week. With the second fall this week, client reports he hit his head but he states it wasn?t a big deal. He is AA0x4, in no acute distress. During RRT, client was on the phone with his doctor?s office and doctor?s office reported that his PSA level was elevated and he was positive for E.Coli in the urine. 911 called by Site Manager, Deryl Bactad, at 0923. Fire Engine #94 arrived at 0942 and report was given to them. Their initial vitals were: HR: 79, BP: 146/106, O2: 98% on RA. Client denies pain and remains AAOx4. He stated he was fine to drive home. Client refused transport to the hospital at 0957. Last BP before paramedics left: 146/95. Client remains AA0x4, no acute distress noted. Client advised to wait in monitoring area for an additional 15 minutes. Client verbalized understanding. Upon leaving, client was AA0x4, in no acute distress, reported feeling fine to drive. Client advised that if symptoms worsen or if he is SOB, to contact his PCP and/or call 911 and/or get to the nearest hospital. Client verbalized understanding of all information given. All questions answered, all concerns met. Client left at 1015 via car, by himself.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: HPI: Pt presents 5-10 minutes s/p initial Moderna COVID-19 vaccination with complaint of numb tongue evolving to perceived wheezing and chest tightness.  No dizziness, shortness of breath, tongue swelling, lightheadedness, chest pain.  Innoculation happened at the left deltoid. PE: VS at presentation: HR 118, SpO2 99%, BP 148/100, no tachypnea, speaks in complete sentences. AAO.  Seems anxious.  Conjunctiva clear.  Mucous membranes moist.  Tongue midline and normal.  No angioedema or lip swelling.  Breathing unlabored, but she is developing an increased frequency of cough during the observation period.  No wheezing initially, developed slight expiratory wheezing during the observation period.  HR tachycardic, regular.  +2 bilateral radial pulses.  Skin flushed on anterior chest, dermatographia on the face, left arm.  Site of innoculation is not swollen, red, or tender.  Able to ambulate.  COURSE: Pt assisted to the acute treatment area and vitals taken. Pt developed cough, she took puffs of her personal albuterol MDI (w/o spacer).  Did not note relief. Provided 25 mg PO diphenhydramine.  Observed. Able to speak in complete sentences.  Says she feels anxious.  Lungs generally clear. Pt perceived need for additional doses of MDI.  I recommended 2 additional. Developed mild wheezing.  Still speaks in complete sentences. Observed.  Stable.  Said she had to use the restroom.  RN escorted pt to restroom.  This also served as a test of exercise capacity and progression of symptoms.  Pt returns feeling more short of breath.  Has expiratory wheezing, increase anxiousness. Administered 0.3 mg IM epinephrine lateral right thigh using aseptic technique.  Provided 25 mg additional PO benadryl. I recommended transfer of pt to the CMC ED for continued workup and observation.  Pt agreed. Bangs Ambulance arrived to pick up the patient.  I provided verbal handoff report to EMT-P.  VS at time of transfer: HR 102, SpO2 99% on RA, BP 140/90.  At time of transfer no wheezing, pt speaking in complete sentences.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On  January 16, the day after being vaccinated (1/15/21),  I woke up with my arms, hands, legs and feet tingling and numb all over and it lasted on and off all day January 16 and on and off all day January 17 and has persisted every day until Monday, January 26 when the symptoms became worse. Instead of tingling in all extremities (with some numbness)  the sensations changed to a pins and needles sensation with burning and random electrical shock sensations. I want to note that, yes, I have radiculopathies  - however, I have never had them change so suddenly and increase in intensity so fast. Also, the pins and needles sensation with burning and random electrical shocks are brand new symptoms for me (my radiculopathies have not presented this way before).  I reported these symptoms to my primary care provider today (1/29/21) and she instructed me to report my symptoms to VAERS and she is referring me to neurology. Note: I received my vaccination outside of my health care system and received it through the county because I could get the vaccination sooner that way.  I did not report these symptoms sooner because they were not listed as a possible adverse effect of getting the COVID19 Moderna  vaccination. However, as these symptoms have worsened over the past 2 weeks I have become concerned.  I have not added any OTC medications or supplements to the ones listed prior. I have gone to a chiropractor twice during this time for relief of my back pain with  no positive outcomes. Waiting to see the neurologist.

Presents to ED with worsening redness and tenderness of his right upper mid thigh.  Patient states that he got the Pfizer vaccination yesterday second shot evening and then developed some subjective fevers sweats and chills.  Also had myalgias this all lasted approximately 2 hours but he was able to get to bed and fall asleep.  Woke up this morning feeling better but still with some chills but noticed some tenderness and redness in his right upper mid thigh.  This got progressively worse.  Continues to have chills but improving.    ED work-up including CBC unremarkable, CMP with mild hyponatremia and hypokalemia of 134 and 3.4 respectively.  ED drew blood cultures and then started vancomycin.  Vitals normal and stable in ED.  Admitted to hospital.  Provider notes on 2nd day of admission as follows.  Cellulitis and abscess of the right medial thigh likely secondary to a skin tag tear which introduced infection.  Patient currently is on broad-spectrum antibiotics in the form of doxycycline and vancomycin.  Unfortunately, the patient has been eating just ate lunch and also has been getting Lovenox.  He is not going to tolerate a bedside incision and drainage.  We will plan on proceeding to the operating room tomorrow for quick I&D and cultures.  Procedures been explained.  The wound will need to be packed afterwards and ultimately healed in.  Patient seems understand plan and we will proceed accordingly

I was absolutely floored at how sick this shot made me.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 24 y.o. female who arrived  to the emergency department for an allergic reaction after receiving the COVID-19 vaccine today. Patient states she received the first dose of the Maderna vaccine in her left arm around 0910 hours this morning. Patient waited 15 minutes afterwards and within 30 minutes was back working in the trauma unit. However, she suddenly began to experience nausea, chest tightness, palpitations, shortness of breath, throat tightness, light headed, and overall shaky. Patient states she further went down to the vaccine clinic to inform them of her symptoms in which she was prompted to come to the ED for evaluation. She was not given an Epi pen prior to arrival. Patient reports overall feeling better now with only continued tingling in her tongue and fingers, as well as feeling mildly light headed. Patient also states her throat continues to feel tight, but denies any throat swelling. Chest tightness and palpitations have since improved, only with occasional flutters in her chest similar when feeling excited. Denies nausea, rash, itchy skin, or abdominal pain. No history of anaphylaxis or allergic reactions. Patient is prescribed Nexium, but denies taking any other daily medications.  Physical exam shows to be unremarkable with no rash or throat swelling/erythema. Patient does not appear in respiratory distress. Lung sounds are clear.   Will order an EKG. Will administer IV Epipen and IV Benadryl.   Differentials: Allergic Reaction   EKG shows NSR with sinus arrhythmia. Otherwise normal with a rate of 87 bpm.   Patient was observed in the ED for 3 hours with improvement of symptoms. Provided follow up instructions to clinic list. Discussed return precautions. Vital signs are stable at time of discharge  Initial Vital Signs [01/28/21 1019] Blood Pressure 132/91 Heart Rate 85 Respiratory Rate 24 Temp 36.6 �C (97.8 �F) Temp src Oral SpO2 99 %

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Starting on the 18th I started having pain and numbness in my limbs and chest. I ended up going to the ER where they tested me for Covid and checked my heart. Everything came back negative. The next day I started having severe muscle weakness to where I couldn't stand for more than 5 or 10 mins without feeling like I was going to fall over. I couldn't hold anything up for long without my arms giving out. I started having muscle twitching all over including in my face. I would also have what I would describe as electrical shock nerve pain all over. I went to the ER again and everything came back okay again. I went to Urgent Care and my MD. My doctor stated after looking at the results from the ER that it was related to the vaccine. I was put on high doses of vitamins to see if it would help my body fight the reaction to the vaccine. I was taken out of work for the week because I literally couldn't do anything.  I took the vitamins for 5 days before I started finally feeling better. I'm okay now for the most part. I still am having muscle twitching and nerve pain, but it is far more tolerable than it was.
LAB_DATA: Covid test on the 18th. EKG Vitamin levels were checked There was other tests. I don't know them all.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Just prior to 5P had left arm pain -that traveled to my hand. At 5PM driving and heart rate went 128 - most likely higher (registered on iwatch). This is abnormal for me as my heart rate is typically in high 40's (marathon runner).  Along with the rapid heart rate felt like throat was closing - like a reaction caused by an allergy.  The rate rate stayed like that for about a minute or two followed by severe chills (chills can be described like when a person comes out of the OR).  I felt like I was coming out of my skin and became dizzy. I became nervous and called 911.  In discussion with the 911 dispatch everything subsided and decided I would continue driving with an intent to going to Hospital.  About 10 minutes later, prior to getting onto I95 the same cycle with increased heart rate followed by chills occurred again for about the same timeframe.  I do not know how far apart the cycle was occurring other than I ended up calling 911 again and Ambulance was dispatched while I was on I95 and I had pulled over.  Approx arrival of ambulance was about 6P Once in the back of the ambulance, I showed no arrhythmia and heart rate was now in the 70's, however I was still having the chills.  Decided to drive home after waiting about 20 minutes in the back of ambulance with no further issues of the tachycardia. Once I was home I continued with chills and a high fever throughout the night.  The fever did not go away until about 48 hours. The chills went away by the following morning. Thursday and Friday have had chest tightness and the feeling of needing to take large breaths to expand chest.  Continue to have moderate headache.
OTHER_MEDS: Vitamin C, Vitamin B12, and D3

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Resident was vaccinated on 12/31/20. Then on 1/14/21 he tested positive for SARS-CoV-2 on routine surveillance PCR testing.  Another resident on the same hall was COVID positive on 1/11/21.  Results of the PCR test were obtained on 1/16/21.  He appeared asymptomatic at that time. Given his COVID positive status, all aerosol generating procedures had to be stopped. Overnight on 1/16/21 into 1/17/21, he had the onset of acute respiratory failure and was transported to the hospital. Per notes, he was put on BiPAP for several hours, but his CO2 level did not improve. Per prior advance directives completed with the resident and his two brothers, he had DNR/DNI orders.  The hospital physician spoke with his brother and the decision was made to  move to comfort care. He was discharged to inpatient hospice and died around 4pm on 1/18/21. This outcome does not appear to be vaccine-related, but death from COVID-19 infection is listed as a reportable event following COVID-19 vaccination.
LAB_DATA: Nasal swab sample obtained 1/14/21 and sent for PCR testing was positive for SARS-CoV-2.

She has no evidence of swelling of the lips, tongue or oropharynx on exam.  She has no stridor or wheezing on exam.  Her pulse oximetry readings are in the high 90s on room air.  She received Benadryl, prednisone and a nebulizers treatment.  She was observed in the emergency department for 2 hours and had improvement in symptoms.  She was discharged in stable condition.

Patient was into the clinic yesterday for his first COVID vaccine.  Patient had no contraindications for the vaccine.  Vaccine was administered to right deltoid.  Patient then was asked to sit in the waiting room for 15 minutes for observation.  Patient was sitting in waiting room and developed shortness of breath and dizziness.  Patient vitals signed were obtained blood pressure was elevated 150s/100, heart rate 120s, oxygen level upper 90's on room air.  Patient was brought to an exam room where he could lay down via wheelchair.  Multiple vital signs were taken during the duration of his time at the clinic.  Blood pressure did come down to 140s/90s, sats remained in  upper 90s, heart rate came down to 70-80.  Patient remained dizzy the entire time.  Patient states that he has a history of idiopathic angioedema as well as a heart stent.  Patient goes on the explain that at different times he can have swelling internally.  He has had this happen several times in the past to his abdomen, saliva glands, tongue, as well as extremities.  Patient and his wife called his primary care physician and MD advised if episode did not resolve to go to the ER.  After waiting in the clinic for around 45 minutes the patients wife decided it would be best to go to the ER.  EMS was notified. Ambulance responded.  Patient was transported via ambulance to ER.    Patient wife was called the afternoon of the incident.  She states that patient was admitted to the hospital for observation.  He was treated with Benadryl, Pepcid, Decadron; CT of head was normal; blood pressure was still elevated; and they were not sure what was the cause of the episode.  I called the patient's wife on 1-29-21 to check on patient again.  His wife stated that he was been discharged home.  They were unsure what caused the episode and to follow up with primary physician in one week.  She states that at one week follow up visit they would discuss the need/desire for second COVID vaccine.  .

He said that I did not need to go see him or go to a clinic or Emergency Room unless I felt worse. (I have progressively felt better).  I left his number and contact information  under the contact information above. However, I had received the shot from the Hospital site.  I am providing this as you were a little vague in your question about contact address. Anyway, my husband took my temperature about 6 pm. I had a temperature of about 93.8. I normally have a temperature of 98.6 F. He used a digital thermometer. However, I did not feel as if I had asthma. I did have a slight headache then and my arm was a little bit sore. Today (the 29th) my temperature is about normal. I do not have any breathing problems, but my arm is a little bit sore where I got the shot. I still have a slight headache, but it's not too bad. I don't need to take medication for it. There is no redness at the site of the injection. I should mention that one of the RN's did look at my fingernails and the color was normal which I assume means no problems with oxygen levels. I am only reporting this because of the extreme dizziness! I felt a lot better after about an hour after taking the shot, drinking the bottle of unflavored (still) water and eating the nuts. My A1C is back to normal today. (and remember I am not currently needing or taking any form of insulin but my doctor has my blood checked regularly and has for many years). I am only putting no on the item number 20 below because I still have a slight headache and a little bit of soreness in the injection site. Today the site of the injection  is not red either.

My heart rate started to slow down but remained somewhat high. they helped me into a wheelchair and escorted me to the emergency department. I was assessed for cardiac concerns and labs were taken. After a couple of hours in the ED the dizziness started to subside but I had excessive thirst and dry mouth and slightly swollen tongue. I had feeling of butterflies in my stomach off an on. My heart rate stabilized and I was cleared to go home after four hours.

12 hours after my second dose I felt paresthesias in my extremities - particularly in my hands and feet - as well as my face. I also had chills and rigors. I felt lightheaded and nearly fainted.  Day 1 post vaccine: I had chills and rigors and the hand/feet paresthesias were persisting. I also felt heavy and weak.  Day 2 post vaccine: the chills had resolved but the hand/feet paresthesias were persisting as well and the generalized weakness got worse. I went to the ER and was sent home with instructions to follow up with neurology. That evening my hands became swollen and tight.  Day 3 post vaccine: the weakness improved but the paresthesias were persisting. I went to work and on my drive home a I felt electric jolts throughout my body but especially my extremities - which caused me to shake. The rigors came back and I also had abdominal pain. Day 4 post vaccine: I still felt similar symptoms but milder than the night before. I got evaluated and tested for covid which was negative. Labwork and U/A were also negative. The symptoms resolved that evening but the paresthesias were persisting and started to become more painful. I had an MRI of my brain and spine which were negative. Day 5 post vaccine: The paresthesias had become more painful. I was started on Lyrica by my neurologist. Day 6 post vaccine: I felt chest pressure and a globus sensation in my chest, weakness, and jolts in my extremities. The dysthesias in my extremities were persisting. I was evaluated by my neurologist had an EMG which was normal and was diagnosed with small fiber neuropathy. I was told to continue Lyrica and titrate the dose up until the symptoms resolve. Day 7 post vaccine:  I have been having heaviness, jolts in my extremities and face, and dysthesias in my hands and feet for most of the day. Lyrica helps a little.  Throughout the entire time I have also had intermittent paresthesias in my face and jolts of pain in my face at times.  I also had paresthesias in my face and intermittent dysthesias in my extremities 7-10 days after my first Moderna dose. Symptoms got a lot worse after the second one. Given the timing I am concerned that these symptoms are vaccine-related.
LAB_DATA: Labwork done on 1/21/21; ESR, CK, iron, CBC, CMP, ANA, Vit B12, TSH all negative CBC, CMP, U/A, pregnancy test negative on 1/26 MRI brain, c-spine, t-spine - normal on 1/26 EMG normal on 1/28

SYMPTOM_TEXT: "I received my second COVID vaccine on  1 20/2021 at 1100. (Pfizer) At 2100 I had a slight headache and body aches and went to bed. I slept poorly and felt as though my heart was racing overnight. When I awoke at 0700 on 1/21/2021, I felt very lightheaded with sitting upright at the side of my bed and ""blacked out""/lost my vision, but was still conscious. I proceeded to lie back down on my bed. I began to feel nauseous and again attempted to sit up to go to the bathroom. I again blacked out. I lowered myself to my bedroom floor and laid there to rest for several minutes and then crawled to my bathroom. I began retching and had emesis of frothy sputum. I then felt the urgent need to have a BM and sat on my toilet, but was again lightheaded. I bent forwards to not pass out and completed the task and then laid down on my bathroom floor to recover. I was gradually able to crawl down the stairs and located my cell phone and contacted a friend. I pulled myself up to my couch and sat for some time. I checked my BP and it was WNLs, but low for me, as I generally take 2 antihypertensives in the AM. I did not take them at all on the 21st. I gradually was able to walk to the kitchen and drank several glasses of water and tea. In addition to these symptoms, I had severe pain up and down my spine, in my knees, shins and buttocks. I applied Thermacare heating pads to my occiput and sacrum. I had no appetite and was very lethargic, napping for nearly 6 hours, on and off. I took Tylenol later in the day when I was able to eat a banana and yogurt. By evening, I had a headaches and body aches, but no more dizziness. When I awoke 1/22/2021, I was not dizzy, but my head felt ""huge"" and ""off"". My body continued to ache severely and I was unable to come to work. Tylenol helped diminish the pain slightly. I was again very fatigued. I did not leave my house, feeling unsafe to drive. By 1400 I felt better and was able to eat dinner that evening. I finally felt safe to take a shower Thursday PM 1/23 I awoke at 0615 to work. I was able to work until 1700, feeling fatigue, but no other symptoms. I did take Naproxen prior to coming to work for low back pain"

Client developed a mild covid infection 12/8/21 and recovered. He was admitted 12/25 with hypogycemia and mild weakness and sent home He was given his first dose of the Moderna vaccine 1/4/21 at approximately 9AM covid vaccine clinic He developed weakness the next day  (1/5) prompting admission to a hospital and then transition to subacute rehabilitation briefly  Work up at hospital revealed progressive respiratory failure and pneumonia requiring intubation and progressive ascending weakness and sensory loss without upper motor neuron changes.  MRI : nerve root enhancement LP : protein 40, +/- 80 lymphocytes, cultures negative B 12 and B6 normal extensive CSF testing still pending campylobacter and Musk antibodies negative Neurology diagnosed likely AIDP (Guillain-Barre) and an EMG is planned for the near future.  Neurology felt the cause of his GBS was likely his covid infection verses his Moderna vaccination He was treated with plasmapheresis.  Client received dexamethasone, remdesivir, and zosyn and doxycycline when progressive leukocytosis and procalcitonin elevation was noted. Candida was cultured from tracheal aspirates but felt most likely d/t colonization with an option to treat further if he did not continue to improve. He is now extubated, unable to swallow and has profound weakness and distal sensory loss. He will transition to Acute rehab in the near future.  Comorbidities:as described in the above section and... DM2, CKD3, HTN, DJD, BPH ( h/o prostate surgery), h/o Lumbar surgery and hernia repair, GERD, hypothyroidism, hyperlipidemia.  Possible etiologies of his AIDP ( GBS)  would include his recent covid infection, the Moderna Vaccine, or other undiagnosed infection. He got his flu shot 9/25 ( fluzone sanofi) so this is not likely to be the culprit

Side effects started the same day I received the vaccine, which were reported on the V-safe app.  Started with very sore arm, within 24 hours progressed to extreme fatigue, joint and body aches, loss of taste and headache. I also experienced some mild nausea. By Wednesday evening, I began to experience heart palpations which I listened to as a nurse which sounded like PVC's. I have never had this happen to me before. I assessed my vital signs and noted that as the arrhythmia progressed, my O2 sat level began to decrease and my pulse began to increase. I could hear a definite pause in my heart rhythm. Within an hour, I had chest pain in the area of my left chest over my heart which progressed into a feeling of pressure as if someone was standing with a foot on my chest. As time went on, this sensation radiated into my back at an angle from left to right. It was at this point that I had my father take me to the emergency room. When I got there, my pulse was in the low 100's and my blood pressure was 230/130. I have never had this happen to me before. I ended up on a nitroglycerin drip. My magnesium level was low and my sodium level was low normal.   I was kept in the emergency room until Thursday evening then transferred to Progressive Care Unit where I remained until early evening on Friday.I was sent home on 2 different cardiac medications, Coreg and Lisinopril. I am to follow up with my PCP and a cardiologist. Both are brand new to me. I am now feeling better, but I am very reluctant to have the second covid vaccine. "I received the Covid vaccine at about 1140 on 1/23/21. I sat for 15 minutes and went to get up I was I little dizzy so I sat back down. I stayed downstairs for another 10 minutes. at 1220 - I then got up with no additional dizziness so I proceeded to go back to my department. It is worth noting that I normally have low blood pressure so I do sometimes get the dizzy light head sensation but it resides by sitting back down and waiting a little bit. For this reason, I did not think of it as a symptom/reaction to the vaccine.  Along the way, I got a little dizzy; different than my normally low blood pressure feeling - this was more of a spinning type of dizzy - hard to get my bearings. I kept on walking to my department as I work in Cancer Care and there was no one in the part I was walking in at that time. In the process I got an intense heat throughout my entire body - it was super hot it felt like a fireball. I then started to get a lump sensation in my throat. I got back to the department and my coworkers said I did not look good at all and had me lay down. I was later told that my face was very puffy and swollen. They stated that I was extremely red and overall not good. There was a definite sense of urgency. I then laid down and we put ice behind my head and the Radiologist came in to look at me. At that time I started to feel a tingling sensation in my throat and neck, I did notice a voice change (my voice was more raspy/airy and was crackling. I could feel my heart beating super fast and hard. At this time I felt like it was hard to catch my breath, I did not have wheezing or a tight chest sensation. The staff member then went to get a nurse from the neighboring department. We did vitals and my blood pressure was very high 168/98 was the very first one. Along with an elevated heart rate of 138. O2 saturation was 98%.  The decision was then made to call a rapid response. The response team came. They did additional vitals that stayed elevated in that range. They did a blood sugar which was around 79.  I was informed that I had a rash on my neck going down my chest and on my stomach. They tried to lay me down, that really bad I could not catch my breath and felt immediately worse, so we sat back up. Upon further evaluation, the decision was made to take me to the ER. I had developed a headache by this time. Upon examination, they noted that I also had a rash on my back. Benadryl and Tylenol were given around 1400. I remained in the ER until my vitals started trending down and the tingling sensation started to go down and my voice returned to normal. I was discharged around 1520. Upon arrival at home (1800) I started to get the tingling sensation and lump feeling back along with a tight chest and cough, along with an increasingly intensifying headache. I took 100mg Benadryl and 800mg of Ibuprofen(1800). This helped the symptoms settle back down. I have been taking 100mg of Benadryl every 4 hours because these symptoms keep coming back. Additionally, my entire body has started to be extremely itchy, onset was around 2000 1/23/21. I was unable to sleep well due to the symptoms returning, headache, and itching. Additionally, until 0200 I was unable to lay down comfortably without feeling like I was SOB. Around 0600 1/24/21 I started with joint aches. At this time I am still taking Benadryl every 4 hours 100mg and 800mg of Ibuprofen about every 8 hours. I have not had a fever. I am closely monitoring the situation along with a family member who is in healthcare. I do have an Epi Pen at home should I need it.

The next worst was the nausea/vomiting, because, well, nausea/vomiting, and especially because there was nothing to bring up. And, unlike vomiting from bad food or something, you don't really feel better afterward, just still nauseated. The other symptoms were more bearable. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 5 minutes after shot my lips were feeling tingly. at 15 minutes out a co-worker sat by me and I told her about my lips and she commented that I had a large red mark/rash on my neck. I went to the nurse and she asked if I was nervous - which I was. She told me that I should take a Benadryl. I took a single Benadryl.  I went home and was still feeling the tingling sensation and had the rash which had spread onto my chest.  I took another Benadryl about one hour after the initial shot. This reduced the rash and tingling sensation. as it wore off about 4.5 hours later the rash, tingling lips and facial swelling started to appear. I took two more Benadryl and called the on call doctor at my physicians office.  He advised me to continue taking Benadryl until 48 hours after the vaccine, I did this every 4-5 hours including waking during the night to keep up on it. I was also taking Advil at this point to try to help with the swelling and a dull headache that had set in. I should note that I have never had any facial injections or anything like unto it. For 40 hours post vaccine I did this. After 48  hours the symptoms seemed to go away. I did start feeling a metallic taste in my mouth that night and the following night so I took a single Benadryl at bedtime those nights and that seemed to resolve it. I have had a slight cough and congestion on days 3-6 when I woke up in the morning, but that would resolve itself within an hour of being up. The doctor on call that I spoke with the first night did advise me to still get the second dose, but to take some Benadryl ahead of time and to make sure that the clinic has a current EpiPen on site.

Patient (DOB 09/20/77) had a reaction to the Moderna Covid-19 vaccine given on 1/29/2021. On the screening form, patient indicated she had allergies. She verbally said she had multiple allergies and had an anaphylactic reaction previously to allergy shots received in a doctor?s office. She said she does carry an Epipen. RPh counseled on the cases of anaphylaxis with the Pfizer vaccine and recommended a 30 minute monitoring period following the vaccine in accordance with CDC guidelines. Patient agreed and received the vaccine at approximately 11:30am with instructions to check back in with RPh at 12:00pm.   A few minutes later (at least 5 minutes), a friend of Patient alerted RPh that patient had fainted. The friend was able to catch patient before she fell off the chair and lower her to the ground. Patient was awake and answering questions but appeared to be having trouble maintaining consciousness. She denied shortness of breath, itching, swelling, and no rash or wheezing was evident. An Epipen was available and present but not administered due to lack of respiratory symptoms. 911 was called at 11:39am with the patient?s permission. Her symptoms remained the same until EMS arrived and she left in the ambulance at 11:57am.

Client received vaccine at 12:00pm after passing risk screening and completing consents at a vaccination clinic event at a local fire station. At 12:09pm, while client was sitting in the waiting area after vaccination as part of the recommended protocol to monitor for adverse events post-vaccination, she began feeling unwell. She started to walk toward the vaccination stations and was stumbling. Staff escorted her to a preassembled cot and had her lie down. The patient reported feeling "tingling" in her face, throat and lips and felt like her lips and tongue were swollen. There was no swelling visually apparent.  Staff called 911, and assessed patient, collected some vital signs (BP 140/90, pulse 83, O2 sats 100,%) and prepared epiniphrine auto injector pen. First responders who were in the fire station building arrived promptly. The patient continued to feel swelling in her throat, but no difficulty breathing . She appeared pale and weak but did not exhibit other signs of anaphylaxis. The healthcare team administered epinephrine in left deltoid. EMS arrived, and team gave report. Care was transferred to EMS. EMS transported patient to local hospital. Patient walked to ambulance without difficulty.

She returned to the EMTs approximately 2 hrs after receiving the vaccine to report  "feeling different".  EMTs witnessed redness on her chest area.  They administered Benedryl and Decadron IV, called 911.  All vitals WNL.  This writer called pt the following day, she reported having been transported to Hospital.  Bloodwork was obtained, she noticed while at hospital that the arm below where injected was covered in a "scarlatina type" rash.  This rash continues to persist, no additional symptoms reported. She was discharged from ER with  Rx for Pepcid and Prednisone and told to f/u with primary.  She saw the PA at her MDs office, and was told to f/u with an allergist.  She intends to go to Medical Center Allergy Immunology for f/u and further advice on receiving second dose of vaccine.  She will follow up with this writer regarding the scheduling/canceling of the second dose based on the consultation with the Allergist/Immunologist.

1.  Out of concern for potential autoimmune reactions to the vaccine, I had some blood tests taken on 12/23/2020 prior to the first dose and repeated blood tests 3.5 weeks after dose 1.  My ANA test has been checked 2 times prior to vaccine and both were negative.  On 1/19/2021, 3.5 weeks after dose 1, my ANA is now positive at 1:80. 2.  On 12/30/2020, the left side of my lower lip began to fasciculate, have paresthesias that were constant from 12/30-12/31/2020.  On 1/1/2021, 2 blisters appeared in the area of the twitching.  I have not had problems with hsv on my lips in the past, so it was very odd to have this occur 2 days after vaccine.    I had concern for hsv reactivation and its association with Bell's palsy given the reports of Bell's palsy in study participants so I called my doctor, discussed my concerns, and asked for and took Valtrex  tid and Prednisone  qd for 5 days, starting on 1/2/2021.  The blisters resolved by 1/3/2021.  The fasciculations improved greatly, but I have had 2 episodes of my lower lip feeling heavy/numb for a few hours since then.
OTHER_MEDS: Singulair , Zyrtec , Restoril  Allergy immunotherapy-last injection 2 weeks prior to vaccination

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Monday, January 25, 2021 - swelling at injection site and extremely tender to touch. Unable to lift arm up or down easily. Tuesday, January 26, 2021- swelling and hardening at injection site and still very tender to touch. At approx. 10 am,  I began experiencing extreme nausea and exhaustion. By 1:00pm I was dry heaving and began a temperature of 99.9 (when I usually run 97.7) with a very bad headache. At 2:00pm I started vomiting very violently, my body was on fire and I was very faint.  Diarrhea  started at this time as well. The headache continued as well as the nausea. I continued to vomit on the hour up until about 8pm. (I have black and blues all over my knees from being on the bathroom floor.) The headache persisted as well as extreme nausea. Soaked through the bedsheets three times over the night while trying to sleep. Too exhausted to take temperature, but I am certain that I had one. Wednesday, January 27, 2021- Could not work. Went to doctor to get a Covid-19 test, just in case. Doctor says what I describe could be side effects of vaccine. Rapid test returns negative.  Extreme exhaustion. Woke up with nausea and a headache and no fever. Extreme exhaustion persists. Could not get out of bed, could not eat. I was only able to drink sips of water.  Diarrhea continued throughout the day. Nausea returned strong at about 5pm and dry heaving began again. Headache returned as well as temperature of 99.9. Soaked through the sheets again this evening. Thursday, January 28, 2021- Worked remotely and I do not know how I got through the day. Diarrhea  continues as well as nausea, headache and exhaustion. Still not able to really eat. Drank Pedialite and was able to eat 2 dry crackers. At about 3pm, dry heaving and nausea. Headache returns. Unable to get out of bed.  Friday, January 28, 2021-  Diarrhea stops. Still experiencing nausea and headache comes and goes. Still exhausted. By 4pm, back in bed with 99.9, body feels hot and headache returns. Soak through sheets once again.  Saturday, January 29, 2021- woke up with just enough energy to report these side effects. Headache is quiet... temperature is normal. Very, very tired. Feeling completely wiped out.

MY REACTION TO THE FIRST DOSE: In March of 2020 I suffered Covid pneumonia and was on oxygen and too weak and short of breath to work for three months.  It took over seven months to return my breathing and strength to baseline. I just checked my lab and I still have IgG antibodies and a negative nasal screen for the virus. One month ago at 9 AM I received the Moderna Vaccine.  About 12 hours later I developed shaking chills and a fever of about 103, pain in my arm from the injection, and severe cough and a VERY WATERY RUNNY NOSE with severe post nasal drip which caused aspiration of the discharge.   I took Tylenol, Afrin Nasal Spray, and a Dulera inhaler and fell asleep.  I woke up at 3 AM and felt well, but at 4 AM I developed an intolerable intractable cough and severe watery nasal discharge lasting about two hours and severe dry heaves from the aspiration.  Afrin nasal spray helped somewhat but I was absolutely miserable for  two hours.    Three days ago I received the one month booster for the Moderna Vaccine at 10AM.   My arm began to become painful but it was tolerable and not relieved by Tylenol. Every time I rolled over at night the pain woke me up but I was able to tolerate it.  Yesterday I woke up with severe constant chills but my temperature was normal.  I felt very hungry and diaphoretic and felt like I had a low blood sugar,  and ate a bowl of rice chex cereal. I felt a little better but a half hour later VOMITED everything up.  I then felt somewhat better and went to the hospital to make rounds.  The nursing staff reported that about half of them called in sick due to the vaccine with severe fatigue, fever, joint pains and headaches.  One nurse reported that all her joints felt like they were on fire.  Four nursing supervisors also called in sick that day.   I then went to my office and my staff said I looked GREEN and insisted I go home.  I did not eat anything but while resting I again had SEVERE VOMITING of my breakfast at about noon.  When I felt stronger I drove home at about 1:30 PM and fell asleep until about 5 PM, still not having eaten anything nor taking fluids. My arm pain went away.  By 7 PM I finally drank some tea and felt stronger and felt like I was not going to die.   It seems that those of use who had the Covid in the past do not tolerate the vaccine and suffer severe reactions. I was unable to find any studies with the vaccine given to patients who already have antibodies.  This lack of data is a real problem.

On the day of the vaccine I had usual arm soreness. For about 1 hour in the evening I had chills and felt nauseous. I felt fine after that. One week later I woke up and my entire arm was very sore. I thought I slept on it wrong. The pain radiated down my entire arm. Later in the morning, my wrist was incredibly sore and throbbing with pain.  Later that evening I started to rub my arm at the injection site and felt a large, hard bump. I looked at my arm and noticed a red rash in the area as well. I called the Health Dept (who gave the vaccine) and they said to ice it and take advil, which I did. The next day the swelling went down a little bit, but the rash area is much bigger & is not hot to the touch. Today is day 3 of this & the rash & heat are the same. It is less painful than the first day of this reaction.  I googled this and I am seeing people call this "COVID arm." It does not itch though.

About 5 minutes after vaccine, rash started to form  near site.  Then I felt like my body was burning from the inside out, sweating, hives, face turned red, itching all over the body, tongue tingling .  I was sent by ambulance to the ER.

About 6pm (day of injection) I started having chills and feeling  achey.  I had a fever of  which went to 100.7 at 3:30am.  (My normal temp is 97.4) I began taking Tylenol ES  that night and Aleev the next day. I had fever (from 98.2 to 99.9), aches and fatigue  the next two days while taking Tylenol ES  every 6 hours.   On the third day  about noon, my fever went back to normal, and has stayed that way.  My upper arm was red and  swollen and painful for the first week.  On the  4th day after the injection the redness was spreading and moving down my arm.  I called one dr. and started taking 4 Aleev a day.  By the 7.th day, I sent photos to my PCP and she had me come into the office.  She was concerned it might be infected since it was spreading down to my elbow, so she gave me  a double dose of antibiotic (500 mg of Cephalexin to take 4 times a day for 7 days).  I finished that on  1/26)  It stopped spreading and gradually the redness went away. The round (quarter sized place at the injection site ) stayed for days after and now the skin is peeling.  The site is still painful if I press on it.
LAB_DATA: I saw my PCP on 1/19 who thought it might be an infection, but really didn't know I talked on the phone to several different doctors and also went in person where I got the vaccine and talked to the Medical Director and showed photos to all.  No one has seen anything like the reaction I had on my arm.  Most do not think it was an infection but a reaction. I will check below that I am recovered, but there is still pain at the injection site. I am concerned as  my Moderna  vaccine lot number is the same as the one that caused problems in another state.  I am also concerned about a worse reaction to the 2nd vaccine.  I would really like to talk to someone!

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Began to have slight wheezing and coughing on Wed afternoon, the day after getting the shot.  Thursday wheezing and coughing increased and woke me up during the night several times.  Cough was productive with clear sputum.  Friday felt very tired all day and coughing and wheezing increased substantially, producing shortness of breath upon any exertion, like going up and down the stairs.  Very tired.  Began to think I'd have to go to see the Dr. because wheezing was significant with every breath.  Cough was racking, increasing through the day into the evening.  At 10 p.m. I began to wonder if I'd make it through the night without calling the rescue squad.  Couldn't take a deep breath or speak a whole sentence with out a coughing jag.  Then, suddenly about 11:30, it just ceased.  The tightness in my chest went away, the coughing with every inhalation stopped and I could take a deep breath.  It was a bit stunning.  Because I had pulmonary embollisms about ten years ago, my lungs have been a weak spot in my body with bronchitis occurring frequently.  I hadn't seen reports of this side effect of the vaccine, so I thought I'd report it.  This morning, Saturday four days after the shot, I am breathing much better, not coughing, and do not have any wheezing.

Then I started to feel compression and pain in my ribs on both sides, and the middle of my chest - like an elephant was sitting on it, or I had a corset wrapped too tightly around my diaphragm. Then I started having uncontrollable coughing fits, followed by wheezing. EMS got me some ice packs for my ribs and the middle of my chest, but I had to get up and use the bathroom.  When I get anaphylaxis, I usually take two aspirin, a benadryl, a cetirizine, a CBD capsule, a famotidine, a 20 mg steroid pill, and a hydroxyzine pill - all at once. EMS agreed I should take it, and they gave me a shot of epinephrine in the arm. then they loaded me on to the ambulance, where I got a shot of steroid, and we went to the hospital in. EMS also started an IV for me. At the hospital, they gave me another shot of EpiPen, over 20 minutes after the first one, and a shot of Benadryl. by the end of 2 hours, my breathing was back to normal, and I was able to go home. Today I still feel a little bit dizzy, but mostly my arm is sore where I got the vaccination. I also still have a headache.

Approximately 60 seconds prior to emergency, patient felt a sense of panic (first time ever).  Stated to me (wife) "I feel like I am having a panic attack" as we walked on to a parking garage elevator at 12:30 pm on 1.22.21.  As I turned to push the button to go down, leaned against the wall of the elevator. His eyes fluttered and back, he was a little pale.  When I turned around, again, he fainted and fell face down on the elevator floor.  He never stopped breathing and had no convulsions.  He was out for less than 30 seconds. When he came to, he got up by himself with minimal assist from me (911 was already on their way).  He did not remember saying that he felt like he was having a panic attack; but he remember the fear/panic he felt just prior to.  He was oriented x3.  I had him smile, stick his tongue out and speak to make sure it was not a TIA or stroke and there were no symptoms of that.  His bladder did release.  He went by ambulance to the ER (we were on a mini vacation to celebrate his birthday). They did a CAT scan, checked his blood sugar twice, EKG twice, complete blood work panels and urinalysis  All tests were either normal or negative.  They found nothing.  His BP was normal for the first 30 minutes at the hospital, then increased.  But has been normal ever since (he checks it daily). Absolutely no other symptoms since that episode.  He met with our PCP on 1.29.21 as a follow-up and she directed us to complete this form. She has ordered a consult with a Neurologist and that is scheduled for 3.10.21.  His second shot for the vaccine is due on 2.9.21.
LAB_DATA: CAT Scan normal Blood Sugar x2 - both normal EKG x2 - both normal Blood work - all tests normal Urinalysis - all negative/normal
OTHER_MEDS: Atorvastatin 20 mg q day Rabeprazole 20 mg 2x day Hydrochlorothiazide 25 mg q day Losartan 50 mg q day

The patient came in to get her 2nd dose of COVID-19 vaccine.  The patient is pregnant and currently enrolled in 2 trials.  She also had COVID-19 back in July.  The patient received Pfizer vaccine today (1/30/2021) as this was the only vaccine being given today.  Upon administration, it was noticed that the patient had actually received Moderna first (12/30/2020 at 9:10 a.m.) and should have received Moderna again.   The nurses stated that they informed the patient that we are giving Pfizer vaccine today. The patient disputed this and said she wasn?t told this information. However, the manufacturer and lot# were recorded on her vaccination card and this was missed before the patient got her vaccination.   In the midst of explaining about the vaccines the patient told us that she rescheduled her own appointment from Wednesday, Jan. 27 to today Jan. 30.  Apparently this was a glitch in our scheduling system and the problem has been fixed.    Patient was advised to contact her OB/GYN and clinical trial coordinators. On day 04 After receiving the 2nd Covid 19 Pfizer vaccine, I experienced a deep pain in my upper inner right thigh around 0600 am of the 16th of January. At the same time my calf muscle of that same right leg was in pain.  I thought it to be muscular pain as I was told by the reading material regarding symptoms of the covid 19 vaccine there could be aches an pains attributed to the 2nd shot.  I used a deep heating rub on both areas of my right leg and put heat on them to treat the soreness.  This occured over the next few days feeling this pain in my right leg and treated the same way applying heat. Within about 24 hours of the pain in my legs I started experiencing a shortness of breath while walking up and down stairs as part of my daily activities.  The symptoms of shortness of breath only seemed to appear when I was on any form of extended walking activity or physical movements or exercise this would of have been starting around the 17th of January.  The right leg pain was masked by the heating rub while the shortness of breath continued for the next few days.  On the 19th of January,  I went to an Urgent Care Facility at 0800 am to see a Medical professional to discuss my symptoms I was previously experiencing and to figure out why I was having a shortness of breath and the pain in my right leg.  The on staff Physician's Assistant had a Nurse conduct a Covid 19 Rapids test (negative) and a second swab was administered and sent to the Lab.  Which produced a (negative for Covid 19) on the 20th of January.  An Xray was not taken to determine my shortness of breath.  The Dr listened to my lungs and heart,  though I did let the PA know I had received both Pfizer shots and when they were administered.  I was carrying My Shot record for the vaccine with the dates and lot number.   He didnt appear to be interested in further diagnosis and made sure I had the paperwork to track the results of my Covid swab sent to the lab. The visit was completed and I was released to go back to work/home.    I carried on the symptoms of the shortness of breath from the 19th of January to the 22nd of January monitoring my O2 (oxygen levels) with a pulse oximeter.  They ranged from 90-93.  On the evening of the 22nd of January I was becoming very uncomfortable with my breathing climbing the stairs in my home and monitored my O2 readings with the oximeter on my finger when walking upstairs and they dropped down to 60-65.  My wife drove me to the emergency room at Hospital.  I walked into the ER and checked myself in for shortness of breath and leg pain in my right leg.  I was admitted into the emergency room and put on 15 litres of oxygen.  The emergency room Dr ordered a chest Xray,  Cat Scan of my chest and heart and a sonogram of my right leg.  The testing results came back with a noted large pulmonary emboli on my lungs/heart area and blood clots throughout my right leg (right lower extremity DVT).    Surgery was performed to remove the pulmonary emboli and I was put on a Heprin Drip to thin out my blood for the remaining clots in my chest and my right leg. The attending physician ordered a T.E.E. (transesophageal Echocardiogram) to observe my heart functions.  I was told the TEE did not demonstrate any further recommend surgeries.  I was administered a test for my cardio and heart functions prior to my discharge on 27 January 2021.   I was prescribed Eloquis for maintenance medication to be monitored by followup visits to my cardiologist and Hemotologist within the next few weeks.  I have not family or personal history of Blood Clots.  I do perform administrative duties as part of my job, which requires sitting and working on a computer.  Note however I move around very often during a work day and operate a farm tractor and have an active life style.  I have not recently had any extended trips more than 2 hours nor have I flown within the past year or so.
LAB_DATA: Blood labs drawn 23-27 January 2021 at Hospital Ultra sound Right leg  for DVT 23 Jan 2021 CT angio  Chest       23 Jan 2021 Xray chest portable  23 Jan 202      Echocardiagram without contrast 27 Jan 20211  transesophagae

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 5 minutes after the vaccine, my tongue began tingling. I drank water but didn't tell anyone at the vaccine clinic. I did wait 17 minutes before leaving. I went to the car to look in the mirror and assess my oral airway. My tongue and pharynx were not swollen. I kept drinking water and proceeded to go home. About 10 minutes into my drive my throat became tight, so I went back and checked into the ER. My vitals were stable, and you couldn't see any swelling. My throat felt tight and my tongue tingly. I had already taken pepcid and zyrtec that morning, so they gave me Solumedrol and Benadryl IV. The tingling and tightness improved and went away by about 0930. It did return around 2300 that night (not as bad, just tongue tingly and slight tightening of my throat), and I took another pepcid and benadryl. I also had myalgias, felt febrile and fatigued for about 48 hours.  ++See previous VAERS report I did about vaccine #1

"Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine EUA" I received my 2nd dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine on Jan. 20th, 2021.  On Jan. 21st, 2021, I woke up feeling feverish.  I went to use the bathroom, and after washing my hands I walked towards the bathroom door and felt light-headed and dizzy.  Suddenly, I passed out and hit my head and upper neck on the tile floor.  My parents heard the sound of my fall and luckily rushed to the bathroom.  They found me lying  unconscious on the floor with my eyes rolled up for what felt like more than a minute.  I regained consciousness on my own, and I drank water with a bit of sugar and salt mixed in.    I felt too weak to get up and walk, and the back of my head and upper neck were in pain.  I told my parents to call 911 as I wanted to make sure that there was no serious damage to my brain or neck area.  I went to the local hospital in an ambulance.  I was taken to the emergency room: Vitals were done and my temperature ranged from then was 99.5-101F and my heart rate was high- it stayed around 112 bpm for some time I was given 2 L of IV Saline Fluids EKG result: no clinical abnormalities CT head/neck/spine: negative 2 different types of COVID-19 tests: results were both negative Bloodwork: CBC/BMP/D-dimer: no clinical abnormalities Chest Xray: negative 2D- doppler ultrasound: negative Holter monitor: negative for irregular heart rhythm I was discharged the same day around 4:30pm

I contracted Covid-19 approx 1 week after getting the vaccine. I do not believe that the vaccine gave me Covid. But, I believe that it made me more susceptible. The week of receiving the vaccine my daily schedule was approx  80-90% covid patients. I do Physical Therapy in a hospital with them and spend approx 30 min or more with each patient.  If I or my facility would have been given a warning  my schedule could have been different.  Our therapy team might have been allowed to change the individual patient load depending on when each person recvd the vaccine. I am older and have a few underlying conditions so I was concerned about contracting it.  Luckily I was able to stay home.  *main take-away is that health care facilities should have been given more information and guidance on how to change schedules to best protect the employees if the vaccine causes a reduction in immunity right after.    I asked the question in a Facebook group for therapists and many of them did get covid right away.  Coincidentally?  Could be. But for sure something to keep track of.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my second dose of the Moderna COVID vaccine at approx. 10:40 AM on Friday, January 29 at clinic. By 12:00 PM, I noticed that I developed facial swelling, which was most significant around my eyes, and I felt lethargic. Between 12:00 PM and 2:00 PM, I  developed hives on my neck, chest, stomach, and arms, which prompted me to take 1/2 of a dose of 25mg Benadryl.  Nonetheless, the symptoms persisted and I began to experience dizziness and tightness in my throat around 4-5 PM, which was when I was advised by a nurse to go to the emergency room for treatment. I arrived at Hospital's Emergency Department around 6:00 PM and I was treated for "Possible Allergic Reaction Major." I received diphenhydrAMINE (BENADRYL) injection 50 mg, famotidine (PF) (PEPCID) injection 20 mg, methylPREDNISolone sodium succinate (PF) (SOLU-MEDROL) injection 125 mg, sodium chloride 0.9 % iv bolus, and acetaminophen (TYLENOL) tablet 650 mg. I was discharged after 10:00 PM and sent home with a prescription for predniSONE 20 mg and famotidine 20 mg. My facial swelling and hives have gone down but neither have completely resolved since being discharged. I am also experiencing full body aches and fatigue at this time (3 PM on Saturday, January 30).
LAB_DATA: Blood draw, blood pressure, pulse rate, oxygen saturation, respiration - all on January 29, 2021.

Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine EUA  After receiving the vaccine on January 18, my arm hurt for the first couple of days, similar to what I have experienced when receiving a flu shot in the past. I didn't/don't feel any pain, tenderness, or itching, and there was/is no swelling. Since then, the center area has lost some of its red color, but overall the red area is larger now (about  6 1/2 x 3 inches as of January 30). The area does not feel warm anymore and I don't have any other symptoms besides the discoloration. I have not gone to see a medical professional as I feel totally fine.   I would like to note that I had a similar reaction  (skin turning red, raised, and warm) 6 days after having had surgery under my arm to remove a cyst in 2019. Back then, the symptoms disappeared within a day or two.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Moderna COVID-19 vaccine EUA- Patient came to the pharmacy on 1/30/21 at 9:15am. Her left arm was red, itchy and swollen. The red area extended 5.5" wide and 3.5" tall. I marked the margins with pen and told her she needed to see her primary care doctor or go to an emergency care center as I was concerned about it being possible cellulitis or an allergic reaction. I also wrote her a note to have her doctor make a determination if she should receive the second vaccine if this was an allergic reaction, and if so, if she should have it in a hospital or doctors office better equipped to handle a severe allergic reaction if one was to occur. She was able to see a Nurse Practitioner at her doctors office. He prescribed Cephalexin 500mg three times a day and took pictures of her arm. The "clinical visit summary of today's visit diagnosis" was "cellulitis of left upper limb, adverse effect of vaccines and biological substances". NP was going to forward the picture and information to her primary doctor Dr. She was told that Dr. would be contacting her on Monday or Tuesday and would make a determination if she should receive the second dose in the Moderna series and if so, if she would have to have it in a hospital type setting.

COVID- 19 Vaccine. She was experiencing chest tightness, SOB, and dizziness. 50mg of Benadryl and 20mg of famotidine was administered around 1410. Patient was still experiencing chest tightness and was having difficulty breathing. 0.3mg of epinephrine was administered at 1420. EMS was called. Breathing improved. Pulse ox 100%, HR 68, BP 130/89. EMS arrived and assumed patient care.  Pt seen in Emergency Room 1/16/2021 1513 CHIEF COMPLAINT: reaction to COVID vaccine   HISTORY OF PRESENT ILLNESS: Patient is a 64y F with PMHx significant for Myopericarditis, Anxiety and HTN who presents to ER after developing tongue swelling, wheezing, tunneled vision and shortness of breath. Patient states that she was getting first shot of COVID19 Pfizer vaccine at 2:00 pm. After getting vaccine she waited 15 minutes like she was told and recalls room getting very hot at approximately 6 minutes after getting vaccine. She also states that her tongue felt swollen. She then noticed her vision started to turn dark and then she felt dizzy. She told pharmacist about symptoms and then she was given one pill of Benadryl. This did not help and actually made her symptoms worse. She recalls wheezing. She was given another pill of what she believes was Benadryl. She also recalls pharmacist measured her BP and her husband, who was present, reported that her blood pressure was in the 140s This did not improve so she was given 0.3mg IM epinephrine shot. This significantly improved her symptoms. However, she was sent to ER.  She denies any hx of recent UTI or GI infection. She denies fevers, chills, nausea, diarrhea, chest pain, generalized itching, vomiting, abdominal pain, generalized swelling, headache or syncopal episode. She denies any past reactions to vaccines. She denies current SOB and feels like her symptoms resolved. Denies hx of COPD or asthma. Physical exam did not show any recurrent signs of wheezing or tongue edema. Her SaO2 was 100% on RA and BP was within baseline 140-160s. Given episode, we decided to obtain tryptase levels. We also observe patient to ensure she did not have any recurrence of symptoms. She remained hemodynamically stable and SaO2 remained in mid 90s to 100. She was given a rx for epinephrine pen should symptoms recur though this is highly unlikely as she remained stable throughout ER stay. She was also given instructions to pick up OTC Benadryl and Pepcid. She does have antihistamines listed as an allergy but patient states that she gets tachycardic upon taking tabs, so this could just be a side effect. We will follow up with tryptase levels but even if tryptase levels return as normal, it does not mean she did not have an anaphylactic reaction to vaccine. Her clinical picture puts this diagnosis high in the differential. Teaching and instructions were given to patient and her husband. She was advised to return to ER if symptoms recur.    IMPRESSION: Anaphylaxis Anxiety attack
High blood sugar, fever, headache, body aches
OTHER_MEDS: Lisinopril, metoprolol, pravastatin, amlodipine, Lyrica, insulin
HISTORY: Type 1 diabetes, gastroparesis, high blood pressure, high cholesterol

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt here today for her second dose of Moderna COVID vaccine. States she did not have any issues with her first dose. Pt does endorse hx of syncope.    Approximately 10 minutes after pt received vaccine, she started to feel dizzy and faint and was slouched over in her chair. Pt pale, flushed, tangibly warm and sweaty skin. Transferred pt to stretcher. Pt endorses that she did have breakfast this morning. Felt slightly nervous about getting the vaccine but not overly anxious.    Vitals taken: BP 95/59, HR 75, O2 99%. Rapid response called. Rapid response nurse arrived at bedside.    Repeat vitals, taken approximately 5 minutes apart:  BP 109/63, HR 96, O2 99% BP 109/63, HR 97, O2 99% BP 114/77, HR 108, O2 99% BP 101/70, HR 99, O2 100% BP 106/62, HR 97, O2 100%   Pt given juice with some improvement in symptoms. Started to feel her hands tingling and had sensation of cold flowing through her body. Feelings of dizziness waxed and waned.    Pt transported to ED by rapid response team for further observation.  ED MD notes: "MDM, ASSESSMENT AND PLAN:  Overall well-appearing 39 year female experiencing lightheadedness after vaccination.  She has no other signs or symptoms to suggest an acute allergic reaction.  This may be vasovagal.  Plan for urine pregnancy test and EKG, consider IV fluids.  Patient prefers not to undergo testing unless completely necessary.  We decided to obtained orthostatic vital signs and if patient is symptomatic and/or showing significant changes in blood pressure or pulse with positional change, then will proceed with limited workup for near syncope.   DIAGNOSTIC STUDIES O2 sat interpretation: normal on RA Equivocal orthostats - HR incr w/ standing but so did BP. Pt states she's feeling better, tolerating po. Again denies poss pregnancy. Prefers to go home. OK to dc, close return precautions.     IMPRESSION: Dizziness. Adverse medication (vaccination) reaction, not allergy."
LAB_DATA: per ED notes, plan for urine pregnancy test and EKG
OTHER_MEDS: synthroid 50 mcg daily (per patient's medical record) albuterol 108/90 inhaler PRN  Astelin 0.1% nasal spray PRN  Pepcid 20 mg PRN
HISTORY: per medical chart: history of tachycardia, history of antepartum hypothyroidism. Also history of advanced maternal age multigravida.  asthma, GERD

SYMPTOM_TEXT: In the first several days following the vaccine I had "normal" reactions such as redness and aching. However, the second Sunday after the vaccine (8 days later on 1/24) I had a very large, red, itchy, area on my arm in that location with small red rash bumps.  Over the next 24 hours it got extremely swollen and inflamed and the skin temperature was 101.8 degrees on the surface.  It developed a painful "lump" under the skin and the area was hard.  The redness increased in diameter and I went to Urgent Care where they wondered if it was cellulitis and put me on an antibiotic.  However, by Wednesday 1/27 it was still red and swollen and I followed up with my General Practitioners office.  They explained that they have seen several of these cases and added a steroid to go with the antibiotic.  The redness is mostly resolved, but settling some near my elbow and still quite itchy.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The patient had received the moderna vaccine and about four days later he started to develop persistent fevers and, within one week, had developed a diffuse, blotchy, erythematous rash. Bloodwork was obtained by PCP which had revealed eosinophilia (AEC peaked 4250) without evidence of end organ damage. He underwent skin biopsy which revealed:  Superficial and mid dermal perivascular infiltrate. Additionally, there are focal interface changes where lymphocytes approximate the dermal-epidermal junction and are associated with vacuolar alteration. A few eosinophils are noted in the infiltrate but they are not numerous. Vasculitis is not seen. These histologic features are not entirely specific, but are most suggestive of a hypersensitivity reaction.  Initially treated with topical steroids. When eosinophil count was noted to be above 4,000 the patient was started on 60 mg of prednisone daily (this was on 1/26/21) and repeat CBC with differential are pending. The rash is improving and fever curve is also improving (on tylenol q8H PRN).  He was referred to hematology/oncology for consideration of bone marrow biopsy, as hypereosinophilic syndrome is also on differential diagnosis.

4 hours after the administration of her COVID-19 vaccine, she developed the onset of twitching of her left eyelid, some left-sided jaw pain, a cotton mouth sensation, and migratory left-sided facial paresthesias described as a tingling sensation that could involve the eyelid, nostril, scalp, cheek, or forehead.  These sensory symptoms feels somewhat like a Christmas tree with lights going on and off in different spots but always restricted to the left side of her face.  In addition she experience a mild headache but without associated scotoma, nausea, vomiting, or vertigo. Upon looking in the mirror she thought that perhaps there is some slight facial asymmetry on the left side.  In addition she reports feeling that her neck is weak on the left side and that she has to support her head in order to keep it from flopping further to the left.  The symptoms have been also associated with some pain in the left arm which has since improved as well as discomfort and achy sensation involving her left leg extending from the hip laterally down to the level of the knee. She was evaluated the next day by a neurologist. Her neurological examination demonstrates some subjective decrease in sensation involving the left V1 and V2 distribution but is otherwise normal.  Difficult to know to what extent the prior Botox injections could be contributing to her worsening left-sided neck weakness.  We are aware that the vaccine does induce a inflammatory cytokine response and it is conceivable that this is contributing to some of her symptoms.  MRI was obtained to exclude any underlying CNS pathology that could be conceivably exacerbated in the setting of an inflammatory micro environment induced by the vaccine.  There was no clear evidence of a new CNS lesion based upon the examination.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient described that they felt like the room was "spinning," and felt "weak." Patient denied any shortness of breath, difficulty breathing, chest tightness, or itching/ flushing.  RN took vital signs at 1400, and were as follows:  155/99 mm Hg, 181 BPM, 26 BPM, and 100.5 F. RN took patient to a secluded area,  and  relaxation techniques (deep breaths, relaxation imagery, etc.) done RN. After relaxation techniques vital signs apical pulse 86 BPM.  Patient indicated she did not feel feverish at home, and no elevated temp. reported at screening station. Patient indicated that she was diabetic and had not eaten since the morning. RN instructed to eat a piece of candy.  Patient also indicated that they have high blood pressure usually, but could not identify approximate values.  Relaxation techniques continued. At 1435 vital signs were as follows:  131/68 mm Hg,  86 BPM, 20 BPM,  pulse oximetry 95%, 100.5 F. RN provided instructions to continue to monitor symptoms, and if worsen seek medical attention. RN provided information to rest, drink plenty of water, and take OTC medication as  clinically indicated.  Patient returned home.

During the 15 minute observation following the 1st Moderna vaccine dose, the patient reported her tongue 'felt thick,' flushed skin, redness on face, neck, hands, BP=98/60, HR=100.  Patient felt 'jittery' and 'heart racing.'  Was transferred to ED for evaluation given that patient reported her tongue 'getting tighter.'  In the ED, the patient was treated with diphenhydramine 25mg x 2 doses, methylprednisolone 125mg x 1 dose, famotidine 20mg x 1 dose, and NS IV fluids.  Hypoglycemia was ruled out with CBG=87.  The physician avoided treatment with epinephrine due to it being listed on her allergy list with a reaction of 'shortness of breath.'  Symptoms resolved over the next 3 hours.  The patient was discharged home with a new prescription of oral prednisone taper.  Subsequent follow-up with her primary care provider, in consultation with an ID provider, recommended that this patient NOT get a 2nd dose.  Covid-19 vaccine was added to her allergy list with a reaction of 'anaphylaxis.'

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Woke up approximately 14 hours after receiving dose #2 with body fatigue. My large joints (e.g., hips, knees, elbows, shoulders) started to develops aches/discomfort. A hot shower helped relieve the initial discomfort, and I took 1g of APAP ~45 minutes after waking up. I then reported to work, which is an ambulatory care clinic that is working a drive-up clinic. As such, I had to work outside in ~20F weather. I had 4 layers on my upper body and 2 layers on lower body with wool socks. The cold did not bother me for the first two hours as I was able to return to a warm area between patients; however, as work became busy, I spent more time outside. The aches/discomfort in my joints progressively worsened as well as the general bodily fatigue. I took another 500mg of APAP, but it did not help much more. Eventually, the cold and body fatigue made breathing uncomfortable, and my breathing became slightly labored. Returning to the warm environment helped the symptoms not get worse, but focusing on tasks became slightly difficult. I returned home at approximately 1630, took another 1g of APAP, and proceeded to sleep from ~1730 until 0530 the next morning. I woke up feeling much better.
OTHER_MEDS: None during time of vaccination. I took 1g of APAP at ~0630, 500mg of APAP at ~0930, and then another 1g of APAP at ~1700.
PRIOR_VAX: Pfizer-BioNTech dose #1: muscle discomfort at injection site, 1/6/21, age 24

CBC, CMP, and TSH were all normal except for mild hypokalemia (potassium = 3.1 mEq/L). Bedside ultrasound was performed as well. Patient received 1L of normal saline and was sent home after about 3 hours with a mildly elevated HR. In the following 24 hours, pt experienced headache, fatigue, and somnolescence, with brief episodes of mildly elevated HR without palpitations.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Anaphylactic reaction, with tachycardia, hypertension, throat swelling/dyspnea, facial swelling, and diffuse hives.

The next two days I had a sore arm. But a week later, the following Monday and Tuesday, I had fatigue and headaches. I put the date as Wednesday because that is when the concerning possible reactions began. I woke with clogged ears feeling very sick. I took Advil Cold and Sinus and arranged to miss work. It felt like a possible ear infection in my left ear. Also my forearms were painfully sore. I had lifted a heavy box up the stairs the afternoon before but the pain in my arms was immeasurably more than ever expected. My ankles were also very tender as I had done a little jogging the day before and I normally walk. As the day progressed I was barely able to get out of bed. Sleeping and just laying there. My highest temperature was 101.25 at 2:45 pm. I had severe chills on and off. I reported these afflictions and was mailed a covid test by Thursday. The test came back negative by Friday evening. Wednesday night my whole body was tender and I had no appetite. I took tons of vitamins and drank tonic tea and took advil and nasal allergy medication. I am still using all of those. Thursday I woke drenched in sweat. My head was mostly cleared just a wet ear and I had a low grade fever on and off through the day. Just touching my body against a surface was painful. Or putting my hand on my hip. My forearms and ankles were no longer worse than the rest. I received my covid kit and taking it to be mailed was the only time I left my house. I was surprised to find extreme difficulty walking down the stairs with muscle strain and pain in my joints. I was not nauseous but had no appetite. Friday I woke up hungry and felt better. No fever. Fatigue and body tenderness but it was better. Saturday my body is only sore on my glands and jaw and back of head. And my muscle is sore in my left arm. The oddness of that being where my shot was given is what makes me wonder if it was an extreme reaction to the vaccine. Maybe it is a flu. I have never had the body pains I try to describe before.
CUR_ILL: Migraine end of december/caffeine withdrawal i believe

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 3mL 23Gx1 inch syringes used to administer Moderna COVID-19 vaccine treatment under Emergency Use Authorization(EUA): I would like to make two product complaints about these syringes. 1. We have consistently only been able to withdraw 9 doses from the Moderna COVID-19 vial when using these syringes. This device appears to have a very large "dead space" as the safety shield is a separate piece which is leur-locked between the syringe and the needle. This large space is likely the cause of the lost vaccine liquid. 2. We had an incident today where the vaccinator injected Moderna COVID-vaccine into the above patient. Upon withdrawing the syringe from the patient's arm, the syringe and safety shield disconnected from the needle and the needle and needle hub remained in the patient's arm, requiring the vaccinator to use his hand to withdraw the needle. The patient did not notice the device malfunction. The removed needle was examined to be intact and was discarded into the sharps container. Patient tolerated the vaccination without other incident. There was no harm to the patient. Syringe REF # 4236, Lot # 4014236, manufacture date 2020-09-23, ex 2025-09-23, GTIN 20351688048827
